# Trainer image — GPU (real training). Rebased on prime-rl's prebuilt CUDA image
# instead of building prime-rl ourselves: it already ships torch, vLLM,
# flash-attn, verifiers and the `rl` entrypoint, all matched to the right CUDA.
# Building prime-rl from scratch here is a multi-stage UCX/flash-attn build and
# fails on small things (e.g. ubuntu22.04 has no python3.12).
#
# Pinned to commit-eb89285 (== the prime-rl revision the rl.toml was validated
# against). Bump the digest to move prime-rl forward.
FROM primeintellect/prime-rl@sha256:d26e88fbefdd9fe093eefb73b64cedd11e4bdc4b6c664839c611499c5602af28

# Root so the read-only-rootfs HOME (=/root, backed by tmpfs in the CVM) holds
# the Tinfoil SDK's sigstore cache, and so we can install into the baked venv.
USER root

# Runtime deps first (rarely change) so editing our code below doesn't bust this
# layer — keeps local rebuilds fast.
RUN uv pip install --python /app/.venv/bin/python \
        fastapi "uvicorn[standard]" httpx cryptography "tinfoil>=0.11.5" \
        datasets jsonschema

# The writing-style env, registered into prime-rl's venv (changes occasionally).
COPY environments /srv/environments
RUN uv pip install --python /app/.venv/bin/python /srv/environments/personal_style

# Our service code (changes most often) — copied last so a code edit only
# rebuilds these tiny layers. Kept out of /app (prime-rl's own uv project) and
# put on PYTHONPATH; `uv run rl` still runs from /app.
COPY tinfoil_llm /srv/tinfoil_llm
COPY cryptobox /srv/cryptobox
COPY trainer_service /srv/trainer_service

ENV PYTHONPATH=/srv \
    STATE_DIR=/state \
    RL_PROJECT_DIR=/app \
    UV_CACHE_DIR=/tmp/uv-cache

EXPOSE 9100
# ENTRYPOINT (/app/docker-entrypoint.sh: ulimit + exec "$@") is inherited.
CMD ["uvicorn", "trainer_service.app:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "9100"]
